lenders.name: Dave
lenders.loan_because:
I travelled extensively in West Africa and the orient with the Navy, organizing health clinics in a number of countries.  I was impressed by the Africans as hard-working people, living in very difficult circumstances.  Microlending works well in these areas where the purchasing power of the dollar is strong, and little is required to start a business.  A terrific way to continue helping those less privileged, perhaps for generations., and doing this person-to-person lending through a non-governmental organization provides a face to poverty.  It is also much less expensive than doing it through an ineffective (and political) government program.

And finally, these people are me.  I've been among them, enjoyed them, and saw their problems and concerns were identical to my own.  To paraphrase Max Lucado, "God changes the world through people like me."
